727452f-a.title: Queens: Myrtle Avenue - 117th Street
727452f-a.text:
Myrtle Avenue, south side, between 117th Street and Jamaica
Avenue, showing the Triangle Restaurant, occupying an old frame
house, formely J. Gunthers hotel (1891). Myrtle Avenue was
formely the Williamsburg and Jamaica Turnpike. The Jamaica
Avenue ''El'' is in the background.
P. L. Sperr  April 23, 1936
NO REPRODUCTIONS
